Description: Core validation logic for pydantic (Avalan PPA pin)
 pydantic-core is the Rust implementation of pydantic's validators
 and serializers. The Avalan PPA ships 2.16.3 because Noble's archive
 does not carry pydantic-core at all, and Debian sid's source
 (2.46.3-1) requires librust-* crate versions Noble does not ship.
 2.16.3 still uses pyo3 0.20.2, which both Noble's rustc 1.75 and
 python3-maturin 1.3.2 understand.
 .
 Built from the upstream PyPI sdist with cargo dependencies vendored
 at prepare time so the dpkg-buildpackage step stays offline.
